==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impartiality
<hw>Im*par`ti*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>impartialit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality of being
impartial; freedom from bias or favoritism; disinterestedness;
equitableness; fairness; <as>as, <ex>impartiality</ex> of judgment, of
treatment, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Impartiality</qex> strips the mind of prejudice and
passion.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impartially</ent>⟦br⟧
